      "body": "Dear HealthTech Innovations Team,\n\nI hope this message finds you well. I am writing to confirm our upcoming meeting regarding the Health Tracking System. This meeting will be an excellent opportunity to discuss the project details, share our insights, and align on the next steps for collaboration.\n\nPlease let me know if there's any additional material or information I should prepare in advance of our discussion. If there are suggested changes to the meeting time or agenda, feel free to share them.\n\nLooking forward to connecting with your team.\n\nBest regards,  \nJane Doe  \njane.doe@gmail.com\n"
    },
    {
      "id": "196d1728c7d4bfdb",
      "subject": "Re: Query on Data Security Measures",
      "from": "jane.doe@gmail.com",
      "date": "Fri, 28 Jan 2022 11:00:00 +0000",
      "snippet": "Dear Team at HealthTech Innovations, Thank you for your prompt response to my earlier inquiry regarding your data security measures. I appreciate the detailed overview you provided, which helped",
      "body": "Dear Team at HealthTech Innovations,\n\nThank you for your prompt response to my earlier inquiry regarding your data security measures. I appreciate the detailed overview you provided, which helped clarify several aspects of your approach to ensuring client data protection.\n\nHowever, I have a few follow-up questions to better understand the specifics of your security protocols:\n\n1. Could you elaborate on the encryption standards you utilize for both data at rest and data in transit? \n2. What certifications or audits does your system undergo to remain compliant with healthcare industry standards such as HIPAA?\n3. Can you confirm if your platform supports multi-factor authentication (MFA) for users accessing sensitive data?\n\nEnsuring robust data security is a critical factor in our decision-making process, and I want to ensure that your solutions align with our compliance requirements.\n\nLooking forward to your response.\n\nBest regards,  \nJane Doe  \njane.doe@gmail.com\n"
    },
